Farabi

This is a web-based Perl editor that runs inside your favorite modern
browser.

This is the successor of Mojolicious::Plugin::Pedro.

Farabi is a web-based Perl editor that runs inside your favorite modern browser.

To start Farabi, please type the following command:

$ farabi daemon

To access Farabi, please type http://127.0.0.1:3000/ after it.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Farabi

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://code.google.com/p/farabi/issues/list

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Farabi

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Farabi

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Farabi

